oric, linguistics, and psychology. Although this study takes up the theory of satire, it develops a new approach to categorize and analyze aggressive writing.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022)08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107345840 cprintz978311072522340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110734478zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110734478zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110734478/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022  aZDB-23-GOA